Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the deployment and control flow of the UnoCash application:

```plantuml
@startuml UnoSD_UnoCash

participant "User" as user
participant "Blazor SPA" as blazor
participant "Azure API Management" as apim
participant "Azure Functions" as functions
participant "Azure AD" as aad
participant "Azure Storage" as storage
participant "Form Recognizer" as formrecognizer

user -> blazor : Access UnoCash app
blazor -> aad : Authenticate user
aad --> blazor : Return auth token

user -> blazor : Upload receipt
blazor -> apim : Request SAS token
apim -> functions : GetReceiptUploadSasToken
functions -> storage : Generate SAS token
storage --> functions : Return SAS token
functions --> apim : Return SAS token
apim --> blazor : Return SAS token
blazor -> storage : Upload receipt using SAS token

blazor -> apim : Parse receipt
apim -> functions : GetReceiptData
functions -> storage : Retrieve receipt
storage --> functions : Return receipt
functions -> formrecognizer : Parse receipt
formrecognizer --> functions : Return parsed data
functions -> storage : Store parsed data
functions --> apim : Return parsed receipt data
apim --> blazor : Return parsed receipt data

user -> blazor : Add/Update expense
blazor -> apim : Add/Update expense
apim -> functions : AddExpense/UpdateExpense
functions -> storage : Store expense data
storage --> functions : Confirm storage
functions --> apim : Confirm operation
apim --> blazor : Confirm operation

user -> blazor : View expenses
blazor -> apim : Request expenses
apim -> functions : GetExpenses
functions -> storage : Retrieve expenses
storage --> functions : Return expenses
functions --> apim : Return expenses
apim --> blazor : Return expenses
blazor -> user : Display expenses

@enduml
```

This sequence diagram illustrates the deployment and control flow of the UnoCash application, showing interactions between the user, Blazor SPA, Azure API Management, Azure Functions, Azure AD, Azure Storage, and Form Recognizer. It covers key processes such as user authentication, receipt upload and parsing, expense management, and expense retrieval.